  "summaries": [
    "<b>Spooky armor</b> is a <linked>Hardmode</linked> post-<linked>Plantera</linked> armor set made from <linked>Spooky Wood</linked>. Wearing the full set increases the wearer's minion capacity by 4 (to a total of 5), along with granting +58% <linked>summon damage</linked> and creating a glowing effect around the character. It requires a total of 750 Spooky Wood to create the full set.",
    "A full set of Spooky armor provides the following benefits:",
    "<ul><li><span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span> +30 / <span class=\"eico i3 i5\" title=\"Old-gen console and 3DS versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Old-gen console and 3DS versions)</span></span> 27 <linked>defense</linked></li><li><span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span> +4 / <span class=\"eico i3 i5\" title=\"Old-gen console and 3DS versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Old-gen console and 3DS versions)</span></span> 3 minion slots</li><li>+58% summon damage</li><li>+20% <linked>movement speed</linked></li></ul>",
    "Stat-wise, Spooky armor is roughly tied with <linked>Tiki armor</linked>, and beaten by <span class=\"eil\"><span><linked>Stardust armor</linked></span><span class=\"eico s i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span></span>. While Spooky armor has noticeably higher bonus damage compared to Tiki armor, this comes at the cost of 5 defense and <span class=\"eico i1 i2 i4\" title=\"Desktop, Console and Mobile versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions)</span></span> a 30% increase to whip range / <span class=\"eico i3 i5\" title=\"Old-gen console and 3DS versions\"><b></b><i></i><span>(Old-gen console and 3DS versions)</span></span> one additional minion."
  ],
